In Week 16, the pattern that had been forming since the start of Trump\'92s second term came into sharper focus. The presidency no longer moved mainly through speeches or bills, but through a dense web of orders, firings, threats, and deals that reached into almost every major institution. The week\'92s events showed a government not simply bending rules at the edges, but working to change who held expertise, who controlled information, and who counted as fully protected by law. It was a week in which the machinery of the state was used both to hollow out the professional core of government and to reward those closest to power, while courts, local officials, and civil society tried, unevenly, to hold a line. That line grew thinner.\
