The same blurring of public and private appeared in the realm of money and foreign influence. World Liberty Financial, a Trump family crypto firm, announced that it would facilitate a $2 billion investment by MGX, a venture arm of the Abu Dhabi government, into Binance using a Trump-branded stablecoin. The Trump Organization unveiled a new Trump International Hotel & Tower in Dubai and a $5.5 billion golf project in Qatar involving Qatari Diar, a state-owned company, despite an ethics agreement that was supposed to bar direct deals with foreign governments. Freight Technologies, a logistics firm, said it would buy $20 million of Trump Crypto to influence trade policy. Large institutional investors increased their stakes in Trump Media despite the company\'92s losses. These deals showed how foreign governments and domestic firms could convert capital into access and favorable treatment, not just speech. The traits \'93wealth buys law, not just speech\'94 and \'93crony capitalism becomes indistinguishable from governance\'94 both moved because the president\'92s private business interests and public decisions were now openly intertwined.\
